label.value: DCLRE1C wt Allele

value.value: Human DCLRE1C wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 10p13 and is approximately 97 kb in length. This allele, which encodes protein artemis, plays a role in the mediation of both V(D)J recombination and DNA repair via nonhomologous end joining. Mutation of the gene is associated with severe combined immunodeficiency Athabaskan type and Omenn syndrome.

label.value: Protein Artemis

value.value: Protein artemis (692 aa, ~78 kDa) is encoded by the human DCLRE1C gene. This protein is involved in nuclease activity that modulates both DNA repair and V(D)J recombination.

label.value: Seborrheic Keratosis

value.value: A common benign neoplasm usually affecting older individuals. The lesions usually arise in the trunk, head and neck, but they can occur on any skin surface other than the palms, soles, and mucosal surfaces. They appear as flat-based papules or plaques. Histologically, there is intraepidermal proliferation of basaloid keratinocytes, acanthosis, hyperkeratosis, and cysts formation.

Gastrointestinal Neuroendocrine Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of gastrointestinal neuroendocrine tumor, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  This classification applies to gastric, small bowel, colonic, rectal, and ampulla of Vater carcinoid tumors; carcinoid tumors of the appendix and neuroendocrine tumors of the pancreas are not included in this classification.
